= section "Derivative Forms" do
  %p The numerals from two to ten have nominalized forms, while two to seven have a number of adverbial forms.
  %p The nominalized numerals function similarly to collectives. They indicate a small group, either animate or inanimate, that is viewed as a unit. The most common inanimate usage is in reference to playing cards: #{t "тройка", "tróika"} “three (card)”. The most common animate usage is in reference to groups of people: тройка “trio, group of three, triumvirate”. They are formed by affixing #{t "-(и)ка", "-(i)ka"} to the stem of the animate numeral. Note that for the numerals four through ten, the <i>-er-</i> suffix reduces to just <i>-r-</i>. “5” also loses its <i>-n-</i>.
  %p The various adverbs exist only up to seven. They fall into three classes: adverbs of comparison, adverbs of intensity, and adverbs of accompaniment.
  %p The adverbs of comparison modify comparative adjectives, meaning “X times as much”: #{t "драже надуоин", "dráźe naduójin"} “twice as expensive”. On its own, it can also mean “X-fold”: #{t "овелицит надуоин", "ovelícit naduójin"} “it will increase twofold”. For two and three, it is formed by prefixing <i>na-</i> “on” to the animate form of the numeral, although in the case of “two” some other alterations occur. For four through seven, they are formed by prefixing <i>na-</i> to the animate form, while reducing the ending <i>-ero</i> to <i>-ro</i>.
  %p The adverbs of intensity modify other adjectives and adverbs, meaning “X as” as in #{t "надуоци сложне", "naduóici slóźne"} “twice as difficult, doubly difficult”, and verbs, meaning “for the Xth time”: #{t "натройци", "natróici"} “for the third time”. It is formed the same way as the nominalized numbers, except the prefix <i>na-</i> is seen in all forms and the suffix <i>-ka</i> is replaced with <i>-ci</i> (or in older texts or dialectically, <i>-ki</i>).
  %p The adverbs of accompaniment clarify how many people are involved in a certain action, indicating accompaniment with verbs of motion and cooperative work with other verbs: #{t "они шли троем", "oní ślí tróiem"} “the three of them went”. For two and three, the forms are identical to the dative-instrumental form of the animate numeral. For four through seven, the ending <i>-rom</i> is added to the the animate stem, an historical variant of the instrumental.
