  %p When adequate fonts are unavailable, a few substitutions are common: Ѳ becomes 8, Ѯ becomes Кс, Ѱ becomes Пс, and W becomes W from the Latin script. Since most of these characters are not typed very frequently, it generally is not a problem.
  %p Traditionally a titlo, a diacritic consisting of a short jagged line, was written over the next-to-last letter in a number. In modern times generally a single, long overline is drawn over an entire number.
